text: Martin Vlček (born 5 February 1996) is a Slovak professional footballer who plays for Púchov on loan from Inter Bratislava as a forward. == Club career == Vlček made his professional debut for AS Trenčín against ViOn Zlaté Moravce coming on as a 90th-minute substitute for Jairo. == References == == External links == * * AS Trencin profile Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:Slovak footballers Category:Slovak expatriate footballers Category:Association football forwards Category:AS Trenčín players Category:FK Inter Bratislava players Category:Mosta F.C. players Category:MŠK Púchov players Category:Slovak Super Liga players Category:2.
